narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would definitely recommend the class to anyone looking for an interesting (though not gutty) non-western history course!

This is one of the most interesting and important classes that I have taken at Yale thus far. In part because the slave trade is one of the ugliest blemishes on human history, and I think that everyone needs to learn about it properly. But also in part because this course will help you put trade and global interaction from 1450 to 1850 into perspective. I had never realised quite what a global world it was during this era, and I think I now have a much better understanding of how the world systems came into being. The class is a lot of work, and the information can be quite finicky, but it is worth the slog.
I would recommend it. Great class especially for the history distribution requirements. It is genuinely interesting.
